exts—from engineering in the Andes to household rituals in rural China, from South African land restitution to migrant living in Moscow, and from elections in El Salvador to online and offline surveillance among political refugees from Uzbekistan and Eritrea—the chapters in this volume interrogate this ‘affective turn’ through the lens of fine-grained ethnographies of the state. The volume enhances the anthropological understanding of the various ways through which the state comes to be experienced as a visceral presence in social life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aAffect (Psychology)xPolitical aspectsvCase studies. 0aPolitical anthropologyvCase studies. 0aState, ThevCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aBeyers, Christiaan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBozzini, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Penny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKendzior, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaszczkowski, Mateusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaszczkowski, Mateusz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMontoya, Ainhoa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinker, Annabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeves, Madeleine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeves, Madeleine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSteinmüller, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311099821440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785337